      <entry xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-entry" xml:lang="sa">
        <form type="lemma">
          <orth notation="SLP1" xml:lang="sa-Latn-x-SLP1" cert="high" resp="#source">ka</orth>
        </form>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-1" n="1">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">is occasionally used alone as an indefinite pronoun, especially in negative sentences ( e.g., no one is a favourite of any one</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-2" n="2">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">no one else knows</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-3" n="3">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">how does he kill any one?) Generally, however, is only made indefinite when connected with the particles,,,, and, in which case may sometimes be preceded by the relative ( e.g., any persons whatsoever</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-4" n="4">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">to any deity whatsoever</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-5" n="5">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">any friends whatsoever</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-6" n="6">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">whatever). The particle, being composed of and, properly gives a negative force to the pronoun ( e.g., without which there is nothing), but the negative sense is generally dropped ( e.g., any one</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-7" n="7">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">no one), and a relative is sometimes connected with it ( e.g., anything whatsoever). Examples of with the interrogative are common</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-8" n="8">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">and are not so common, but the latter is often found in ( e.g., any one</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-9" n="9">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">some</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-10" n="10">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">no one</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-11" n="11">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">nothing whatsoever</def>
        </sense>
        <sense xml:id="mw-pwg-pwk-ka-sense-12" n="12">
          <def xml:lang="en" cert="high" resp="#machine">any one whatsoever</def>
        </sense>
